### 1. Tool Loop & State Persistence

Your requirement is to use flat JSONL files (`~/.bridge-runner/logs/<ts>.jsonl`) to persist a hybrid of raw messages and internal runner events.

**The Risk: Strict AI Role Alternation (400 Bad Request)**
Anthropic’s API enforces a strict conversation protocol: `user` -> `assistant` -> `user` -> `assistant`. Your `loadMessagesFromTranscript` in `src/runner/run.js` attempts to rebuild this state, but it is highly vulnerable to "role collapsing."

If you resume a session where the last event was a `tool_result` (which is mapped to a `user` role), and your code explicitly appends the new CLI prompt (`messages.push(buildUserMessage(...))`), you will send two consecutive `user` blocks to Anthropic. The API will reject this immediately.

**Architectural Fix:**
In `src/runner/run.js`, you must merge consecutive messages of the same role before sending them to the bridge. 

**Concrete Recommendation:**
Update `loadMessagesFromTranscript` to dynamically reduce arrays:
```javascript
// In src/runner/run.js (around line 96, before returning messages)
const mergedMessages = [];
for (const msg of messages) {
  const last = mergedMessages[mergedMessages.length - 1];
  if (last && last.role === msg.role) {
    // If both are arrays of blocks, concat them. If text, join them.
    last.content = Array.isArray(last.content) 
      ? last.content.concat(msg.content) 
      : [last.content, msg.content].flat();
  } else {
    mergedMessages.push(msg);
  }
}
return mergedMessages;
```

