If you execute this system, treat `--allow-shell --accept-edits` as equivalent to **Remote Code Execution (RCE) with the permissions of your logged-in OS user**.
To truly prevent network exfiltration when executing code generated by an AI, rely on OS-level isolation (like Docker). Do not try to solve bash sandboxing in Node.js. 

